            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>Greenwald said that his interest in the project stems from the connection between religion, gospel music especially, and jazz, a link that too often goes unnoticed and unexplored. It&rsquo;s a thread that&rsquo;s clear to the elder Blade.</p>
<p>&ldquo;[Music] calls for participation on the part of the people,&rdquo; the pastor said. &ldquo;When worship becomes a spectator thing, it loses its meaning and worth.&rdquo;</p>
<p>And this is an appreciation Brian has clearly inherited from his father.</p>
<p>&ldquo;It teaches you so many fundamental things without you necessarily even being conscious of it,&rdquo; Brian said. &ldquo;I think it just gave me the bedrock necessary to ground me in every other situation I would be a part of: how to listen, how to serve the song, how to submit yourself to the moment and be able to improvise and shift as the spirit moves.&rdquo;</p>
<p>Even more than this, <em>The Hallelujah Train</em> will serve as a testament to the importance of gospel music, an art that has never achieved much commercial acclaim. Although a set list hasn&rsquo;t been finalized, there will be some compositions from Lanois and Fellowship Band member John Cowherd. But <em>The Hallelujah Train</em> will primarily include classic gospel songs presented in a fresh context.</p>
<p>&ldquo;There&rsquo;s this essential thread through [the music]&mdash;even if it&rsquo;s new, it makes it seem like it&rsquo;s always existed,&rdquo; Brian said. &ldquo;It&rsquo;s just manifesting itself differently now. We&rsquo;re going to try and have our version of our life experience come through in some of these old songs.&rdquo;</p>
<p>To boot, all of this will happen at the Hayti Heritage Center, a deconsecrated African Methodist Episocal Church.</p>
<p>&ldquo;I just couldn&rsquo;t imagine doing true gospel projects in Reynolds,&rdquo; Greenwald said. &ldquo;In a sense, having access to Hayti was a reason to do the project.&rdquo;</p>

                                                    <div class="related my-4 py-4 d-print-none">
                                <h3 class="kicker mb-4">Read more</h3>

                                                                                                                
            
        
